  "doc_id": "21754",
  "text": "We were able to produce many types of polarization singularities: V-points, where the orientation of linearly polarized states is undefined; C-points, where the orientation of polarization ellipses is undefined; L-lines, where the handedness of the ellipses is undefined; and a type of Stokes singularity where two Stokes parameters are undefined. The only singularity that we were not able to reproduce with our method was the monstar (see for example [CITATION_1] ). This is because we limited ourselves to Laguerre-Gauss eigenmodes for the component spatial modes, but mixing superpositions with opposite polarization states should provide the proper setting. Thus, our method can be used as the basis to study all types of polarization singularities. To our knowledge, this is a first demonstration of a method to produce any polarization singularities on demand.",
